# Claude Code Skill Tree
### A personal learning path for PlotKeeper & beyond

This document tracks your progress with Claude Code techniques. Check off skills as you try them, add your own notes on what worked, and use it as a living reference. Keep this file in your repo alongside `CLAUDE.md`.

---

## How to use this

- **Status:** `[ ]` not tried · `[~]` in progress · `[x]` confident
- **Notes:** Add your own observations under each skill — what prompt worked, what didn't, gotchas
- Work through tiers in order. Each tier builds on the last.

---

## Tier 1 — Foundations
*You're already here. These are documented for completeness.*

- [x] **Basic feature prompting** — Ask Claude to build a component or page
- [x] **Mockup server** — Run a local HTML server to preview UI ideas in the browser
- [x] **CLAUDE.md** — Project context file that primes Claude at the start of every session
- [ ] **PRD-driven sessions** — Write a Product Requirements Doc first, hand it to Claude as the spec. Prevents scope drift and keeps sessions focused.
  - *Try it:* Before your next PlotKeeper feature, write 10–15 lines describing the feature, the user goal, and what done looks like. Open a new Claude Code session and paste it as your first message.

