## Tier 3 — Design Ideation Workflows
*Beyond the mockup server.*

### 3a. Multi-direction design sprints
- [ ] **Three-direction component sprint** — Ask Claude to produce 3 visually distinct versions of a single component as separate self-contained HTML files. Pick a direction, then build from it.
  - *Prompt template:*
    ```
    Generate 3 distinct visual designs for a [PlantCard component].
    Each should be a self-contained HTML file with inline CSS.
    Direction A: minimal and data-focused
    Direction B: rich and illustrative, earthy feel
    Direction C: your own bold interpretation
    No shared assumptions between files.
    ```

- [ ] **Design token audit** — Share your `tailwind.config.ts` and ask Claude to critique whether the colour tokens are being used consistently across components, or whether there's drift.

### 3b. Interactive prototyping
- [ ] **Fake-data prototype first** — Before implementing a complex feature, have Claude build a fully interactive HTML prototype with hardcoded data. You UX-test it, then hand the prototype back as the spec for real implementation.
  - *Try it:* Build the Tasks system as a prototype before writing any Next.js code

- [ ] **Responsive preview harness** — Ask Claude to wrap a component mockup in a three-panel layout showing mobile (375px), tablet (768px), and desktop (1280px) side by side in one HTML file.
  - *Prompt:*
    ```
    Wrap this component in a responsive preview harness showing it at 375px, 768px, and 1280px simultaneously. Use iframes or CSS scaling.
    ```

### 3c. Visual auditing
- [ ] **Screenshot critique** — Take a screenshot of your current UI and paste it into Claude with your design spec. Ask it to identify inconsistencies, accessibility issues, or deviations from your intended aesthetic.
  - *Try it:* Screenshot the PlotKeeper dashboard and ask Claude to critique it against the earthy/calm palette spec in your CLAUDE.md

- [ ] **Component spec sheet** — Ask Claude to generate a single-page HTML visual reference of all your UI components (buttons, cards, badges, inputs, status chips) in every state. Use it to spot inconsistency and document your design system.
  - *Prompt:*
    ```
    Generate a component spec sheet for PlotKeeper. Show every reusable UI element in all states (default, hover, active, disabled, empty). Use the garden-* colour tokens. Make it a single self-contained HTML file.
    ```

