## Tier 4 — Agentic Workflows
*Orchestrating Claude to run parallel or sequential tasks without hand-holding.*

### 4a. Subagents basics
- [ ] **Understand the /agent command** — In Claude Code, `/agent` spawns a subagent that works on a scoped task and reports back. Learn when to use it vs. a regular prompt.
  - *Rule of thumb:* Use subagents for tasks that are self-contained, have a clear done state, and don't need your input mid-way

- [ ] **Codebase audit agent** — Ask Claude to spawn an agent specifically tasked with finding unused files, duplicate logic, and dead imports across the repo. It reports a list; you decide what to delete.
  - *Prompt:*
    ```
    Run an audit agent on this repo. Task: find (1) files with no imports pointing to them, (2) any logic duplicated across more than one file, (3) any components defined but never used in a page. Report findings only — make no changes.
    ```

- [ ] **Parallel design agents** — Spawn two agents simultaneously: one generates a mobile design, one generates desktop. Compare and merge the best ideas.

### 4b. Agent + MCP combinations
- [ ] **Schema + migration agent** — Agent uses Supabase MCP to read current schema, then drafts the SQL migration needed for a new feature. You review before running anything.

- [ ] **Test coverage agent** — Agent reads your existing test files, maps which components/functions have no test coverage, and drafts the missing tests for your review.

