## Tier 5 — Claude as a System
*Everything working together with zero re-explaining per session.*

- [ ] **Session startup ritual** — Define a standard opening prompt you use at the start of every Claude Code session that loads CLAUDE.md, confirms the active task, and states what Claude should NOT do without asking.
  - *Example:*
    ```
    Read CLAUDE.md. Today's task is [X]. Do not modify migration files or seed data without confirming with me first. Ask before creating new components — check if one already exists.
    ```

- [ ] **End-of-session handoff note** — At the end of every session, ask Claude to write a 5-line summary of what was changed, what's in progress, and what the next session should pick up. Paste it into a `SESSION_LOG.md`.

- [ ] **Automated context refresh** — Set up a GitHub Action (or just a local script) that regenerates a `REPO_SUMMARY.md` on every push — file count, component list, table list — so Claude always has a current map of the repo without you maintaining it manually.

- [ ] **PRD → prototype → implementation pipeline** — The full workflow: write PRD → Claude builds interactive prototype → you sign off → Claude implements from prototype as spec → tests written alongside. No feature skips any step.

